I drank pretty much a fifth of gin every night for a number of years. I wanted to quit, but each night I opened the bottle again. I finally called a rehab facility and told them I wanted to come in. They said I could be there in a few hours.

I drank several bears, then went over when scheduled. The rehab clinic handles drug users as well. When I arrived they had me strip to my underwear and to make sure I wasn't bringing in drugs. I felt very humiliated, and low life at that moment.

I had to stay in the clinic for a week. the exterior door to my wing was locked and I felt like I was in prison. But, they insure that you can't go out to get drunk/high. They kept me sedated and I was in a daze the entire week. They had us attend AA meetings while I was there, and classes on addiction. Some classes I skipped because I was so sedated... I was crashed out and in bed.

After I was releases I didn't really want a drink again. For me, I just needed to prove to myself I could stay sober.

I still drink on a very limited occasion, maybe one drink every two months. I can drink a beer, and not want another. It's now been about 10 years since I went sober.
